&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Brooklyn Nets Basketball Operations &lt;/strong&gt;department is seeking a passionate, innovative, and collaborative &lt;strong&gt;Full-Stack Basketball Systems Developer&lt;/strong&gt; to design and build software solutions that improve the efficiency, connectivity, and decision-making capabilities of the team&#39;s Basketball Operations department.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This individual will work across the full software development lifecycle—from planning and architecture through deployment and ongoing maintenance—building applications that enable the Brooklyn Nets to make faster, smarter, and more informed decisions. The ideal candidate thrives in an environment of ownership and autonomy, enjoys solving complex technical problems, and is passionate about creating intuitive tools that have a direct impact on an NBA franchise.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW102866689 BCX0&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW102866689 BCX0&quot;&gt;This position is part of Brooklyn Sports &amp;amp; Entertainment but is dedicated exclusively to the Brooklyn Nets Basketball Operations department. Unlike many roles that support multiple business units across the organization, this position works directly with the Brooklyn Nets every day, building technology and systems that power basketball operations and competitive decision-making.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP Selected SCXW102866689 BCX0&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU WILL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop, deploy, and maintain full-stack web and mobile applications that improve the efficiency and effectiveness of Basketball Operations workflows.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable internal software solutions that support player evaluation, scouting, coaching, roster management, and front office decision-making.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Basketball Analytics developers to plan, architect, develop, test, and maintain basketball software applications.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with analysts and data scientists to integrate player evaluation models, predictive analytics, and basketball metrics into user-friendly applications.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop intuitive user interfaces that emphasize usability, performance, and thoughtful user experience for coaches, scouts, and front office personnel.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and extend complex software systems while identifying opportunities to improve architecture, scalability, and maintainability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in technical design discussions, code reviews, and collaborative development processes using GitHub and modern software engineering best practices.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build secure APIs and backend services that support data integration across Basketball Operations systems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot production issues, optimize application performance, and continuously improve software reliability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on emerging technologies and recommend innovative solutions that provide a competitive advantage for the Brooklyn Nets Basketball Operations department.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
